parameters:
\n<Ameria>"I know. Geez... I went and sorted out the talk all by
myself, and here you are, taking it easy."

\n<Lyric>"It's not my fault. Besides, how long do they expect us to
wait just to enter the castle? It doesn't make sense."

\n<Ameria>"Can't be helped. They can't just let people come and go as
they please. The castle in the 'Central City' is especially
strict with security."

\n<Ameria>"...Alright, it seems like they've given us the go-ahead, so
let's hurry. We're past the scheduled time."
\n<Lyric>"Ah-... No, just thinking what nice weather it is."
\n<Ameria>"Huh? What's wrong, do you have a fever?"

\n<Ameria>"We've been on edge for so long, it feels like it's been a
while since we've had a chance to talk like this."

\n<Lyric>"That's true. But you need to be careful. There are some
oddballs out there who would say they want to buy you."

\n<Ameria>"But that was surprising... I wonder who it could be?
Someone who wants to buy me."

\n<Lyric>"...Well, probably the magic book did something about it.
It's not often you find someone interested in such a tiny
thing like you."
\n<Ameria>"You've been making fun of me this whole time..."

\n<Ameria>"Oh, but you know. It seems like the empire is going to
properly search for the slave trader who came to kidnap us.
They know his face and name, so if they find him, we might
learn something about Begieade too."

\n<Lyric>"Hmm... But don't get your hopes up too much. That guy will
probably keep a low profile for a while."

\n<Ameria>"I see... But still, with all that's happened, the empire is
sure to find some clues. The name 'Riolano' is pretty
unusual too."
\n<Ameria>"...? What's wrong? Do you know something?"
\n<Lyric>"...No way. I couldn't possibly know anything about that."
\n<Ameria>"Right. I hope they catch him soon..."

\n<Ameria>"--Wait, this isn't the time for this! We need to go now,
hurry up!"
